TextBlock.TextLine: 24 Juny 1694
Londen Wall & wile kent
on the 21 curt was to you my last with copyes of my letters of 7 &
10 ditto which am soory did not reached your handes for I finde
by yours of 5 ditto that I have onley to exspect with the ostend
convoy 4 pack, 3 there of with spalclothes, & a monghts all then
not one fine cloth, principally the chest nust cullours, & some
upon the draps of about 14 ƒ, neither one darck gray, of 8 a 9p
so that you send mee what I doe not much want, which troubless
mee, so I will onley have to be send mee p the vere first convoy
the 2 superfine chestaat cullours, & 2 ditto mixt with a litble
white, a vere darck chestuit drap with the 2 fine new cullnts
so N 14 & no more sill
ƒ11 a 28 N 3 of samen dato p
of the 7 cur, with 2 a 3 darck grayes, the nest mest
or de
on other omored convoy, butt I have then vere ill, not to abseve

the 5 northrens att hull according to your formar advise
were readdy above 4 weeke agoe & might have been shipped
without the 12 p ordered 24 mey, interim itt zeems that
the amst convoy from hull bee arrived, trade so is vere
dull, co that I am not much encouraged to im order anneythingh
more from the nord, as yett & from london ouley what I have

J July 1692
Amst geerd Rover
volgens de ue van 24 & 23 pas dencke myne 2 packen voor nu versonden
daerentusschen met de laeste engelse brieten hebbe ick het in vengaende
cognossement becomen van noch een pack N53: gelaeden in tschip
van thomas haworth van inhoudt & weirde als N 48 t'welck vervolgen
oock gelieft te lichten, & over ter gouda my toeseynden, onse schepen van
londen naer ostende derven niet afcommen om dat 8 a 10 franse oorle
schepen onder Jan bart op onse eust hrujssen, het convoy van hull op
Rott was oock seylreede, godt will die bewaeren te is een schande dat
die van hollant & Engelandt gedrogen dat de fransen een schip nem
& daerentusschen sij doen wat sij willen op 7 pas hebbe ick ue met
sulg gerecommandeert den ingesloten op londen, dogh hebt ongeluck
gehadt dat den selven met brieven van 11 maer is voorts gegaen, & &
neffens de andere inse door die van tgenomen pacquet boot in
dee geworpen te is dene ongelegentheyt voor ons de t wij een
ander moeten moeyelyck vallen onse brievven addies te geven &
bidde in toecommende prompter expeditie, & naer groet & gelyck aende
ingeslotene terwijle bek
J Julij 1694
Leijden hendrick Hermantze
volgens den ue van 25 pas verwaghte ick het laken N 15 ick en
twijfele niet ofte gij hebt dat wel laeten heet persen gelyck ick
begeire dat aen alle d'andere oock geschiede nu moet gij alleen van
Laureijs ka N19 ontfangen, & seynt my al & seffens & als deee
gedaen sullen sijn, dan sult gij myne rekeninge seynden, dat ick ue
dan weder eens betaele & de verven waer op gij moet letten geljck
ick ue voordesen heb geschreven, dat sy 8 ten hondert laeten corten
waer mede blyve

Londen Wall & Will Kent
My last to you was 24 past, to which referre you, in answer to yours of
8 & 12 d the ships from hull are arrived att amst: I wish I might
writte as much of those for ostend, butt they are debained because o Jan
bart with 8 a 10 french ships cruriseinge upon our coast, god send
them well, & preseve from losse: by my formar letters you will finde
what you have to provide viz flo 1 pack to containe flannels & swanckens
bacjes, & the worster frises, which must come for ostend, so gett them
in the market
eaddy by times & made such cullours, as you doe not finde, & lett them
vee made up in 2 packs least the next ostend convoij should tarry to long
then could I have one pack for holland, if you examen my letters &
principally that of 1d you will finde out how manney sp clothes bee
wantinge to compleate my orders, principally that of 20 mey last to which
boright
IAinde as yett 2 p viz one to N beeinge N 262, & 1 toN3
beenge N 274, so that there is 5 p wanting fo that order: 1 gray of
13 a 14 ƒt of the order of 3 june, 2 chestant cullours of 3 ƒp to the
patt N1 of 17 mey so there is 8 p wantingh of forrmar orders
besides what I writt for 7 & 10 past all which you may prepare
for the first convoij for ostend & doe all what you can to procure
the 2 superfine chestuut culens & 1 a 2 d dro darck & browne
draps with the 2 ney cullours, which 5 a 6 p must bee of 13 a 14 d
with the dark grayesiso as I writt you by my last of 24 past, which
must come by the vere first convoj for holland, wonderinge much
that all this time you could not finde & brownes of 14 p they
could have been made his, I hope you shall send mee some of
them by this first convoy for Rott from london, because I have
so long sence promised the brownes & browne draps, butt the browne
draps must, have a little white as possible, bee of a chest it brown
